Reviewed lifecycle mapping treats CREATING as
provisioning, UPDATING as updating, ACTIVE and
INACTIVE as success, and DELETING as
terminating; FAILED is terminal and DELETED is
only a delete-confirmation target.
Create and delete responses expose work-request
headers, while UpdateAnalyticsInstance returns
only opc-request-id plus the resource body. The
runtime records shared async breadcrumbs from
lifecycle projection rather than polling
GetWorkRequest directly.
Only description, emailNotification,
licenseType, freeformTags, definedTags, and
updateChannel reconcile in place. FeatureBundle
and KmsKeyId stay in required status projection,
but supporting SetFeatureBundle or SetKmsKey
remains out of scope for the published runtime.
DomainId remains a create-time input that is
read back into status. AdminUser and
IdcsAccessToken are create-time inputs OCI does
not echo back, so they are normalized out of
post-create parity checks.
Required status projection keeps
NetworkEndpointDetails, PrivateAccessChannels,
VanityUrlDetails, updateChannel, featureBundle,
domainId, and systemTags on the published kind,
and the runtime has no secret side effects.
end note
